---
// src/pages/services/wine-cooler-repair.astro
// Audit pass 2026-04-23 (C15 PRIMARY HYBRID, DUAL-SERVICE-HUB novel pattern, 3rd audit-primary application):
// Schema Pattern A migration (body <script> → Fragment slot="head-scripts"), phone (323) → (424) primary,
// tier H2 structure + brand-index, cross-links DOWN to 7 new combo pages + 1 Sub-Zero combo ✅,
// cross-links UP to C14 Built-In + C13 Freezer matched-column suite + sibling SIDE to /services/wine-cellar-repair/.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

// Phase 3 batch 3 (2026-04-27), neutral multi-county hub. Per audit-output/rewrite-plans/wine-cooler.md:
// title/H1/eyebrow/subtitle neutralized; areaServed = 5 counties; aggregateRating removed per
// wiki/decisions/nap-rating-policy-ssot.md. Recent Repairs NOT redistributed, page's competitive
// moat is luxury brand hierarchy + vibration/sediment angle, both of which a 2-LA+1-OC+1-Ventura
// rewrite would dilute. Cities-served block swapped to 5-county clusters.
const title = "Wine Cooler Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Wine cooler + cellar repair across SoCal. Sub-Zero, Viking, Miele, Liebherr, Thermador, U-Line. Thermoelectric + compressor. EPA 608. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/wine-cooler-repair/";
const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = "+1" + MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');

const faqs = [
  { q: "How much does wine cooler repair cost in Los Angeles?", a: "Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most wine cooler repairs run between $120 and $320. A thermostat, door seal, or fan motor replacement is toward the lower end. Compressor work or control board replacement on premium units like Sub-Zero, Viking, Miele, Liebherr, or EuroCave runs higher, we provide a written estimate before any work begins. For wine cellar repair (walk-in room-scale cooling), see our sibling /services/wine-cellar-repair/ service hub." },
  { q: "My wine cooler isn't cooling, is it the compressor or something else?", a: "It depends on the type of unit. On a thermoelectric wine cooler, 'not cooling' is almost never a compressor problem, these units use a Peltier module, not a compressor, and they have an important limitation: they can only cool about 20°F below the ambient room temperature. If your unit is in a warm room or unconditioned space, it may simply be unable to reach wine storage temperature regardless of whether anything is broken. On a compressor-based unit, not cooling points to the compressor, condenser fan, thermostat, or refrigerant. We diagnose the actual cause before recommending parts." },
  { q: "What is the difference between thermoelectric and compressor wine coolers?", a: "Thermoelectric coolers use a Peltier module, no moving parts, no vibration, very quiet. They're excellent for collections where vibration is a concern. Their limitation: they can only cool about 20°F below ambient temperature, so they struggle in warm rooms and can't function properly in unconditioned spaces. Compressor coolers work like a small refrigerator, they can maintain wine storage temperature regardless of room temperature, but produce some vibration. For serious collections in LA, where ambient temperatures can be high, compressor units are usually more reliable." },
  { q: "What's the difference between a wine cooler and a wine cellar?", a: "Wine cooler (this page) = appliance-scale unit. Freestanding, built-in, or undercounter; 15-180 bottle capacity; 15\"/18\"/24\"/30\"/36\" widths; plugs into an outlet. Brands include Sub-Zero, Viking, Miele, Liebherr, Thermador, True Residential, U-Line, Gaggenau, EuroCave. Wine cellar (sibling /services/wine-cellar-repair/) = walk-in room-scale cooling system. 500-10,000+ bottle whole-room cellars; custom-built conditioned rooms; HVAC-adjacent refrigeration with ducted split systems, through-wall units, or self-contained cellar coolers. Brands include WhisperKool, Wine Guardian, CellarPro, Breezaire, Vinotheque. Choose by bottle count and installation scale, 180 bottles or fewer = wine cooler; 500+ bottles = wine cellar." },
  { q: "My wine cooler has zones that are cooling differently, what's wrong?", a: "Uneven cooling across zones in a dual or multi-zone unit usually points to a failed zone fan motor, each zone has its own fan that circulates cooled air. A thermostat or temperature sensor that's drifted in one zone, or a damaged door seal allowing warm air to enter a specific section, can also cause temperature variation between zones. On Sub-Zero IW-24 / IW-30 dual-zone units, the three-way refrigerant valve (which directs refrigerant flow between zones alternately) can also stick, causing one zone to run cold while the other warms. We test each zone independently before recommending parts." },
  { q: "Does vibration from a wine cooler actually affect wine?", a: "Yes, over time, particularly for aged wines with sediment. Vibration agitates sediment, keeps it in suspension rather than allowing it to settle, and can disrupt the slow chemical processes involved in wine aging. A wine cooler that's suddenly become loud and vibrating, often from a failing compressor or a loose fan, is worth repairing promptly for a collection you're aging. Thermoelectric units are preferable for sediment-sensitive bottles precisely because they have no moving compressor parts." },
  { q: "Do you repair all the luxury wine cooler brands?", a: "Yes, seven luxury column + undercounter brands have dedicated combo pages with brand-specific diagnostic orders, parts-chain detail, and model family coverage: Sub-Zero (424/427 + IW-18/24/30 + UW-24 + 315W) · Viking (VWUI/VWUO undercounter + VCWB column) · Miele (KWT 6312/6834/K 2801 + Pro disambig) · Liebherr (HW/WU/WS German specialty) · Thermador (Freedom Collection wine preservation T24UW) · True Residential (TWC/TBC Anaheim LA-local) · U-Line (1000/2000/3000 series specialty undercounter) · Gaggenau (400 Series RW402262/200 Series RW414364 BSH ultra-luxury). Plus Perlick, Marvel, EuroCave, Vinotemp, and mass-market brands serviced via our broader refrigeration service network." }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "Wine Cooler Repair",
    "name": "Wine Cooler Repair, Same Day Appliance Repair",
    "url": canonical,
    "description": "Same-day luxury wine cooler repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Sub-Zero, Viking, Miele, Liebherr, Thermador, True Residential, U-Line, Gaggenau column + undercounter specialists. Peltier thermoelectric and compressor architectures; single, dual, and tri-zone service. $89 residential diagnostic, applied toward repair.",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
      "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair",
      "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/",
      "telephone": phone,
      "priceRange": "$$$",
      "openingHoursSpecification": [
        { "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday"], "opens": "08:00", "closes": "20:00" },
        { "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": "Sunday", "opens": "00:00", "closes": "00:00" }
      ]
    },
    "areaServed": [
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Los Angeles County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Orange County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Ventura County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"San Bernardino County"},
      {"@type":"AdministrativeArea","name":"Riverside County"}
    ],
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, applied toward repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Wine Cooler Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 80px 24px 64px; text-align: center; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 20px; max-width: 820px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #ccc; max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto 32px; line-height: 1.6; }
  .cta-row { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-secondary { background: transparent; color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.35); }
  .section { padding: 72px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-number { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  h2.section-title { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .section-black h2.section-title { color: #fff; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text); max-width: 720px; }
  .section-black .lead { color: #ccc; }
  .intro-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .intro-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .intro-body p { margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-box { background: #fff8e7; border: 1px solid #f0d070; border-radius: 8px; padding: 18px 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .tip-box .tip-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #a07000; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .tip-box p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #5a4000; margin: 0; line-height: 1.65; }
  .sticky-cta { position: sticky; top: 24px; background: var(--black); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 24px; color: #fff; text-align: center; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-label { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-phone { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; display: block; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .sticky-cta .btn-cta { display: block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-sub { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #888; }
  .cta-divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid #222; margin: 18px 0; }
  .cta-detail { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #aaa; text-align: left; }
  .cta-detail li { margin-bottom: 6px; list-style: none; padding-left: 18px; position: relative; }
  .cta-detail li::before { content: "✓"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; }
  .compare-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .compare-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .compare-card { background: #111; border: 1px solid #222; border-radius: 8px; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .compare-card .compare-badge { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .badge-thermo { background: #1a3a5a; color: #6ab0ff; }
  .badge-comp { background: #3a1a1a; color: #ff8a8a; }
  .compare-card h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .compare-card p { font-size: 0.88rem; color: #c8c8c8; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .compare-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .compare-list li { font-size: 0.84rem; color: #c8c8c8; padding: 5px 0 5px 20px; position: relative; border-top: 1px solid #1a1a1a; }
  .compare-list li::before { position: absolute; left: 0; font-weight: 700; }
  .pro li::before { content: "✓"; color: #4a9a4a; }
  .con li::before { content: "✗"; color: #9a4a4a; }
  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 36px; }
  .problem-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 24px 20px; }
  .problem-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
  .tier-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 22px; }
  .tier-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 20px; }
  .tier-card.active { border-left: 4px solid var(--red); }
  .tier-card h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--text); }
  .tier-card .tier-sub { font-size: 0.76rem; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .tier-card p { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.55; margin: 0 0 10px; }
  .tier-card a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; }
  .tier-card a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .sibling-block { background: #f6f2ea; border-left: 4px solid #a07030; padding: 26px 30px; border-radius: 6px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .sibling-block h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 12px; color: #5a4000; }
  .sibling-block p { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #333; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .sibling-block a { color: #a05000; font-weight: 700; }
  .vibration-block { background: #0a0a14; border: 1px solid #1a1a2a; border-radius: 10px; padding: 36px 32px; margin-top: 36px; }
  .vibration-block .vib-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: #8888cc; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .vibration-block h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .vibration-block p { font-size: 0.93rem; color: #c8c8e0; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .brands-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .brand-chip { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 18px; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; }
  .brand-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }
  .brand-chip.dark { background: #1a1a1a; color: #ddd; border-color: #333; }
  .pricing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 36px; }
  .price-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 24px 20px; text-align: center; }
  .price-card .price-label { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .price-card .price-amount { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .price-card .price-desc { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }
  .price-note { margin-top: 20px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .faq-list { margin-top: 36px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 22px 0; }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin: 0 0 10px; }
  .faq-item p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .nearby-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .nearby-links a { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 0.87rem; color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
  .nearby-links a:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; }
  .bottom-cta h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.4rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .bottom-cta p { color: #c9c9c9; margin: 0 0 32px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
</style>

<ServiceHero
  title="Wine Cooler Repair, Southern California"
  subtitle="Sub-Zero · Viking · Miele · Liebherr · Thermador · True · U-Line · Gaggenau. Thermoelectric or compressor, single or dual-zone. $89 diagnostic. Same day across five SoCal counties."
  heroImageTitle="Wine Cooler Repair"
/>

<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Wine cooler repair across SoCal requires knowing which type you have.</h2>

        <p>Southern California has a serious wine culture. From Malibu to Silver Lake, from Newport Beach yacht-club cellars to Thousand Oaks family kitchens to Temecula vineyard tasting-room support equipment, our 5-county service area has one of the highest concentrations of wine collectors in the country, and wine coolers range from a 12-bottle countertop unit to a 180-bottle Sub-Zero or EuroCave that cost more than most appliances in the house. When something goes wrong, the collection is at risk.</p>

        <p>The first thing our technicians establish on a wine cooler call is which type of unit you have, thermoelectric or compressor, because the failure modes, the repairs, and even the diagnosis of "is this broken or just inadequate for the environment" are completely different between the two. A thermoelectric unit that isn't cooling may not be malfunctioning at all; it may simply be operating in an ambient temperature that exceeds its design limits. A compressor unit in the same situation has an actual mechanical failure.</p>

        <div class="sibling-block">
          <h3>🍷 Wine cooler vs wine cellar, two different services</h3>
          <p><b>Wine cooler (this page)</b> = appliance-scale units. Freestanding + built-in + undercounter; 15-180 bottle capacity; single cabinet that plugs into an outlet. Brands: Sub-Zero, Viking, Miele, Liebherr, Thermador, True Residential, U-Line, Gaggenau, EuroCave, Vinotemp.</p>
          <p><b>Wine cellar</b> = walk-in room-scale cooling system. Custom conditioned rooms; 500-10,000+ bottle whole-room capacity; HVAC-adjacent split / ducted / self-contained cooling. Brands: WhisperKOOL, Wine Guardian, CellarPro, Breezaire, Vinotheque. Different service entirely → <a href="/services/wine-cellar-repair/">/services/wine-cellar-repair/</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-label">🌡️ Temperature Risk While You Wait</div>
          <p>Wine exposed to temperatures above 70°F for extended periods begins to degrade. Above 80°F the damage accelerates significantly. If your wine cooler has failed completely and you have a valuable collection, consider moving the most important bottles to a spare refrigerator set to 55°F while we arrange service. It's not ideal for the wine, but it's better than ambient temperature on a warm LA day.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Same Day Wine Cooler Repair</div>
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="cta-phone">{phone}</a>
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-cta">Call Now, We Pick Up</a>
        <a href="/book" class="btn-cta" style="background:#222; margin-top:-4px;">Book Online</a>
        <div class="cta-sub">Mon–Fri 7am–9pm · Sat Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Sun closed · Phone answered 24/7</div>
        <hr class="cta-divider" />
        <ul class="cta-detail">
          <li>$89 diagnostic, applied to repair</li>
          <li>90-day warranty on parts &amp; labor</li>
          <li>Luxury column specialists</li>
          <li>Sub-Zero, Viking, Miele, Liebherr</li>
          <li>Thermador, True, U-Line, Gaggenau</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

